# Java Style Guide

## File Structure

You must:
- Create one top-level class per file
- Name file exactly as class name
- Order: package statement → imports → class definition
- Separate static imports from regular imports with blank line
- Group imports: org.springframework → java/javax

You must never:
- Use wildcard imports (import java.util.*)
- Place multiple top-level classes in one file

## Formatting

You must:
- Use 2 spaces for block indentation
- Use 4 spaces for line continuation
- Set max line length to 100 characters
- Place opening brace on same line (K&R style)
- Always use braces for if, else, for, while (even single statements)
- Add space after keywords: if (, for (, catch (
- Add space around binary operators: a + b, x == y
- No space inside parentheses: (condition) not ( condition )
- No space inside brackets: array[0] not array[ 0 ]

## Naming

You must use:
- Packages: all lowercase, dots separate words (app.luqma.backend.service)
- Classes/Interfaces: UpperCamelCase (RecipeService, RecipeRepository)
- Methods: lowerCamelCase, verb phrases (findById, calculateCalories)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for static final (MAX_RETRIES, API_URL)
- Variables/Parameters: lowerCamelCase (recipeList, maxRetries)
- Type Parameters: Single capital letter or name with T suffix (T, K, V, RequestT)

## Required Practices

You must:
- Add @Override annotation when overriding methods
- Write Javadoc for public classes and public methods
- Handle caught exceptions (never leave empty catch blocks)
- Access static members via class name, not instance

## Java 25 Features

You must use:
- Simplified main: static void main(String[] args) (no public)
- Sequenced collections: recipes.getFirst() not get(0)
- Unnamed variables: catch (JsonException _) for unused exceptions
- Records for DTOs: public record RecipeRequest(String query, Integer maxCalories) {}
